caption: The staff was friendly and observant. It has a cool interior.
you will not be disappointed in the menu and service. i'll return with my relatives. the bill was good for what you get.
nothing to complain about. i will probably become a regular. this place has a good design.
I love the sandwiches and the atmosphere
The sandwiches are really good, but the customer service needs a lot of work. Some of the employees are flat out rude and seem annoyed you're there.
Very good sandwich shop.  If you're not a fan of crusty bread you may discover you like it here.  I am a fan of this style, so kudos and thank you.
Prime rib was awesome. Mac and cheese was bland but good lunch!
Always a happening spot because of their location.  Staff was great and food is good!  Will definitely go back in the future!
New prime rib sando is on point
Excellent experience!  The two gentlemen behind the counter were courteous and professional. Our food was great, clean place. Would love to come back!

Stopped here, wanting to grab a quick lunch while visiting the waterfront. My meatball sub was one of the best I ever had. It was well seasoned, crispness to the bread, and the meatballs tasted fresh. This is definitely not a subway sub at all. Quick, priced Right, and a nice atmosphere.
Great to go meal or sit down! Wonderful staff, right on the harbor!
Great sandwich shop, with a great view of the Harbor!!
Tasty sandwiches!
Good food and service. Not the best soup but sandwiches are on point.
Fast service, good food, reasonable prices especially for the Inner Harbor area.
Great food!
This is a great spot for delicious food, and the staff was accommodating.
It's okay, a nice change of pace from subway, the a wreck sandwich is the best one imo
Menu is hard to read due to placement. Staff was friendly, sandwiches are made fast and were pretty tasty. We ordered the wreck, turkey club and a mixed Berry smoothie. We enjoyed it all.
My first time here since I'm from the West Coast.  This store would do well in the Los Angeles area.   Good sandwiches that are full of flavor.

This was disappointing. Essentially an overpriced subway will smaller portions. I got the Pizza sandwich, which in theory sounded amazing. Meatballs, capicola, pepperoni, mushrooms and sauce. However there was probably a total of one meatball cut into small pieces on the whole sandwich (picture shows a half). I actually had to take the sandwich back up and ask for lettuce and tomato, which I normally wouldn't put on a sauce based sandwich, just to add some substance to it. So $7 got me a burnt piece of bread with sauce and meat bits. Besides that, it has pretty limited choices. Mac and cheese was okay. The salads I saw other people eating looked pretty good.
Great sandwich, nice service.
I ordered chicken salad slim sandwich and it didn't look at all like the photo. Too much bread and not enough chicken salad.
My son described it as "subway with better bread"  i had the Italian sub and jalapeno chips. It was a solid sandwich. No complaints.
This places isn't nearly as crowded as other places along Harbor Place.  The sandwiches are a little better, but a little smaller than Subways, and their shakes are good.
Fast and Super Friendly

Friendly staff and the roast beef sandwich was terrific. The place wasn't as busy as some of the other restaurants. Not a knock against the restaurant but it meant there was seating and a place to get out of the sun.

Quick, kind, clean and convenient. This potbelly location (inner harbor by Hard Rock, Crabby Dick's and Chipotle) is cozy but not cramped. The room gets good light and the seating is open in a way that you can take that in. There is also limited outdoor seating with a nice view of the Aquarium. Staff is always friendly and quick. I prefer their potbelly sandwiches to those made at the Pratt street location. Update: This has really become my favorite Potbelly location by a mile! James and his team really go out of their way to make sure everything is just right. I know Potbelly is a franchise, but James really runs it like a family sandwich shop. Terrific customer service!!
Not bad...but best part about the experience is by far the location.
Wish it had no onions
Great sandwiches made fast.
Slamming!!
Staff were friendly & fast. Had a meatball sub & I was great!!
Soup and sandwiches they were good.
Sandwich was good. Shake was great. Cookies are usually good, but this time was stale.
Great food. Great place
Pretty good.  Very similar subs to Jimmy John's not a real stand out.
I recommend the Wreck on wheat. Servered warm, it is one of the best sandwiches they have. Also add a dream bar for a sweet delight.
Great lunch spot

This place is terrible. Staff is pretty much never up front and you have to wait for someone to come out of the back or yell 'hello??!!' for service. They are rude and I saw a guy lick mustard off his finger when making a person's sandwich.  They also do not do online ordering, the last time I checked.  The soda machine seems like it's always out of something and you can see the mold on the dispensing nozzels.  Stay away from this place.

Stopped there for lunch to try this place out. Staff was incredibly friendly and the sandwiches were great. If you like spicy stuff, their hot peppers are actually hot. They also have Voodoo Heat chips. We also tried out the cookies and they were probably the best sandwich joint cookies I've ever had.

The manager declined our service 15 minutes before they closed and said chips and drink only and then rolled her eyes and said actually were closed now. She was a bigger Latino lady and proceeded to laugh with her co worker as we walked off and said yea I’m Not serving them before we close they can go eat Fin McDonald’s. Hopefully you look at the cameras and she loses her job. Will never use your chain again.
Great costumer service.

After waiting around ten minutes on the line and ordering Chilli bowls and sandwiches the cashier informed me they don't serve chilli today and I should order something else. Two employees didn't inform us! Waste of time and still hungry.
Great service.  The soup is very good.

The sandwiches are not bad at all.... but even when the staff is trying to be nice they should do their best trying to be kind, welcoming and especially communicative with the customers.... otherwise you don't know if you're getting the right sandwich, or even the one you are asking for.
Great food , not so great customer service!!
Good subs made fresh
No trays for six months??!?!  Get it together guys.
Great food friendly staff
Good food and service. Great view of the harbor.
Nice vegetarian options and servers were friendly!
People were nice, but very bland sandwich.
Great sandwich, friendly staff, reasonable prices.
The staff was incredible!! We went for our field trip and the line was out the door with very loud middle schoolers. I would have been stressed and not friendly. I was very impressed!!
Food was good, service great!
Always a great time.  Add Fleet Week and the Thunderbirds...5 Stars doesn't come close
Always great service and good food. Hard to find sometimes in a touristy area like the inner harbor.
Great chicken salad salad and friendly staff

Price was the only thing I could say that was good. Half of my sandwich was burned, other half... not even toasted. HOW DOES THAT HAPPEN!? Loud, dirty, yes DIRTY. Floors were sticky, displays had hardend food particles on them, refrigerator for drinks looked like it hasn't been cleaned in a while.... yeah, this place needs a good cleaning. We ate after ... way after lunch rush so there was no reason for tables not to have been wiped down and trash on floor.

I've been here about 5 times for orders I've placed online and gone to pick up. The food has only been ready once. One time I ordered the farmhouse chicken salad and there was no chicken. Whoops! The girls working the register are never very friendly or attentive. The food, when put together properly, is pretty good though.
Tasty food! And very friendly staff!

I'd leave zero stars if I could. Came into town for a concert and was looking for a quick bite. The woman working there was standing at the order station. When we walked in she walked to the other side of the store and started cleaning with ear buds in. She never made eye contact until after waiting 15 minutes we decided to leave. Then she looked up with a smug look on her face. I don't know how this place stays in business with these kind of emplyees. Save yourself some time and don't bother walking in the door.

This place really annoys me. 1 time out of 5 separate attempts have I actually gotten my food delivered. Almost every time i go on the site to order for delivery they say they cannot deliver at this time.  My job is very demanding and it is hard for me to get away from my desk which limits me to what I can get delivered. I really wish potbelly would be more reliable with their delivery service. I love the food but I can never get it. They have lost lots of money with me because if i can't get it delivered I cannot order it at all. Very disappointed.
Your standard potbelly. It was quite busy when I went (Friday afternoon) so you have to be lucky in order to get a seat.
Rude service here. Very unprofessional. Cell phones on food prep surfaces, sticky tables, dirty floors.
Cool place with okey service
Decent food, decent price, decent service. Normal potbelly.
Solid spot for a quick sandwich
This place is horrible. The manager doesn't talk to the  consumers with respect.  I wouldn't recommend that anyone go tho 1 n. Charles location

Amazing!!! The sandwiches here are delicious and so are the enormous fries. I usually get a medium sized sandwich since it's already pretty filling to me since I get the fries too. The fries are so different from other places because of how big and delicious they are and that's what I love about them. The service is quick and attentive too. It gets busy sometimes so make sure to come earlier!!

Sandwiches were yummy, as usual.  Nice, cool place to get refreshed at a decent price while doing the boat tour in Baltimore.

good malt and potato soup

Two stars bc of course the ingredients quality is controlled by a corporate office and their supply contracts but employees looked like they were miserable and would much rather be anywhere else but here doing anything else but this. Couldnt even get a  "you're welcome" or my smile returned after thanking them and wishing them a good day. I just feel so sorry that certain people are stuck in jobs they can't stand and that we the consumer allow food chains like this one to ignore the most basic concepts of customer service and common courtesy.

This place is filled with workers that clearly hate their job. Horrible service compared to all the other fast food places near the area.  Got a sandwich but half of it almost had no meat.  When I went to ask about it, the guy said this is how they make their sandwiches.  And when I asked for the Manager he first said he was the manager but then said the manager was not there at the time.... if I wasn't in a hurry to leave I would have waited for the manager.  Will never get any food from this place again.
It's okay. Nothing great

Get the wreck. Soooo good and chili.

Good food, pretty quick, no problems with service. Can sit outside or in. No one was really cleaning tables, but that was about my only issue.
Really good sandwiches, but they're a little small and a tad pricey. Great malts, and a very friendly staff.
Decent food, limited seating, a little too crowded..

I expected a lot of Pork and BBQ (not a lot of BBQ here, though the BBQ sandwich was excellent), but they have a little bit of everything actually (flat breads and Mediterranean). Decor was nice, staff was very friendly, and soda is self serve.
Really poor customer service, unprofessional, I will never go back again.

I ordered the Wreck and it was awesome!

The sandwiches there are moderately priced, good enough for anyone looking for a quick lunch. Unlike previous reviewers, I had no "bad" experiences with customer service. Sure, they could have been a bit more joyful, but it was fine.
Ok service.. better quality than Subway

After taking my daughters to the Aquarium, we were starving. We came to this place at 8:30pm, when they closed at 9. One of the attendants literally hung his head when he saw us come in. The other guy told us that since they were close to closing they didn't have any salads, soups or shakes. All three of the staff were rude and acted so bothered that we were inconveniencing them that it was uncomfortable and infuriating. Anything we asked of them was met with eye-rolling and frustration. The customer service we experienced was THE worst. At one point, one of the cashiers literally walked away from his register because of his frustration -- with paying customers.  I would not eat at this place again on principle. The sandwiches were on par with subway or Quiznos, the environment was pretty nice, but we sat outside since we felt so unwelcome.  About 5 minutes after we ordered, we stepped back inside to get some napkins and saw 3 customers waiting at the front, looking for someone to help, with the staff nowhere to be found. (probably all in the back hiding so the customers would go away).  Considering that in this economy there are a lot of people that don't have jobs, these employees don't deserve theirs.
